      "eligibilityCriteria": {
        "eligibilityDescription_md": "\n1. The applicant should be a citizen of India.\n1. The applicant should be a domicile / permanent resident of the state of Punjab.\n1. The applicant should be from Below Poverty Line (BPL).\n1. The applicant should be from the Scheduled Caste category.\n1. The annual income of the family of the applicant (from all sources) should be ₹ 67,649/- per annum (for rural areas); ₹ 88,756/- per annum (for urban areas).\n1. The applicant should not already be availing the benefits of the scheme.\n\n",
